Interview:
Application support and maintenance involve monitoring, troubleshooting, and improving software applications after deployment to ensure they run smoothly, remain secure, and meet evolving user needs.

Application Support (Day-to-Day Operations)

This focuses on keeping the system running without issues:

Resolving user issues (login errors, bugs, access problems)
Handling tickets and incidents
Monitoring system performance
Troubleshooting errors
Ensuring uptime and availability

Application Maintenance (Long-Term Improvements)

This focuses on enhancing and updating the application:

Fixing bugs permanently
Updating features or functionality
Improving performance
Applying security patches
Adapting to new business requirements

Types of Maintenance
Corrective → Fix bugs
Adaptive → Adjust to new environments (OS, tools)
Perfective → Improve performance/features
Preventive → Avoid future issues

Real Example
User can’t log in → Support (fix immediately)
App is slow → Maintenance (optimize performance)
